article:
China issues vehicles licence plates () at its Vehicle Management Offices, under
the administration of the Ministry of Public Security.

Hong Kong and Macau have their own administrations on licence plates. Vehicles
from Hong Kong and Macau are required to apply for licence plates, usually from
Guangdong province, to travel on roads in Mainland China.

The number of registered cars, buses, vans, and trucks on the road in China
reached 62 million in 2009, and is expected to exceed 200 million by
2020.
